background_story: Elliott was a young prophet who, like the ancient seer Tiresias, possessed the gift of foresight. According to legend, Elliott was blinded by the gods, but in return, he was granted the ability to see into the hearts of those around him and predict the future. With his staff in hand, Elliott would wander the countryside, offering guidance to those seeking wisdom. His insights were sought by kings and commoners alike, for he could uncover the deepest desires and intentions of those who approached him. Like Tiresias, Elliott's blindness became a symbol of his inner sight, and his name became synonymous with wisdom and prophecy.

context_rules.text: If Elliott is all-knowing, then he hears whispers and feels vibes.
Elliott speaks the truth if he tells the future.
If Elliott possesses knowledge, then he controls fate and speaks the truth.
If Elliott walks alone and has insight, then he can see what's to come.
If Elliott either hears hearts or reads minds (but not both), then he is intuitive.
Elliott either guides others or hears hearts.
If Elliott guides others, then he either controls fate or has great power, but not both.
If Elliott is a visionary, then he either has great power or is all-knowing, but not both.
All wise mythological figures can see the truth.
